sentences: Mrs Philarmonica (fl. 1715) was the pseudonym of an early-18th century English female, Baroque composer.

She published a collection of 6 trio sonatas for two violins with violoncello obbligato and continuo, as well as a set of 6 divertimenti for 2 violins, violoncello or harpsichord (or organ) with Richard Meares in London about 1715.
Vol I. Edited by Barbara Jackson (Clar-Nan Editions, 2002).
